    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-08T03:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-08T03:34:00-05:00" n="459"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/607</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the Advisory Commission of Railway Experts to
                        Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJF1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-08T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 10, 9.25 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am ready and willing to immediately go ahead with the plan of operating the
                    railways which evolved after long negotiations. I have asked Ambassador
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">Morris</persName> to complete formalities as
                    early as possible. Myself and service corps are ready to act at once.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
